    "caption": "Tiny, fast, and surprisingly good at cleaning up.",
    "shortDescription": "Shrimp live in oceans, rivers, and lakes all over the world, and some of them run actual cleaning stations on coral reefs — fish line up and let the shrimp pick parasites right off them. When a shrimp wants to escape fast, it flips its tail hard and rockets backward in a blink. Fun fact: Some shrimp species can make a snapping sound with their claws loud enough to stun small prey — like a tiny underwater gunshot."
